DIFFERENT TYPES OF DATA:
(1) volunteer data :- you know such data is being stored about you
(2) infered data:-is analysis or conclusion drawn from that observed data cradit card socre.
(3) observed data :-is data directly captured or measured like networkdevice status,user location.

THE BIT
Computers use binary codes to represent and interpret letters, numbers and special characters with bits.
A commonly used code is the American Standard Code for Information Interchange (ASCII). With ASCII, each character is represented by eight bits. 
 cuz the human readable lang must be converted into bits for computer CPU to understand.

ISP
all computers connected to network that participate directly in network communication are classified as hosts. hosts can send and receive msg on the network.
